SEARCH

All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
About
The About class represents a panel that displays information about the game.
AnimationListener
The AnimationListener interface provides callbacks for animation-related events.
Character
The Character class represents a character sprite in a game.
Exit
The Exit class represents the exit panel displayed when the game is exited.
Game
The Game class represents one instance of a game in a JFrame, managing all other classes through JPanels.
GameButtonUI
The GameButtonUI class is a custom button UI that provides a specific appearance for game buttons.
Item
The Item class represents an item in the game, which is a type of Sprite.
Level
The Level class represents a level in the game.
Level1
Represents the first (learning) level of the game.
Level2
Represents the second (maze) level of the game.
Level3
Represents the third (escape) level of the game.
LevelListener
The LevelListener interface provides callbacks for level-related events.
LevelSelect
The LevelSelect class represents a panel that allows the user to select a game level.
Lose
The Lose class represents a panel that is displayed when the player loses the game.
Main
The Main class represents the entry point of the program.
Menu
The Menu class represents the main menu of the Fever Fighters game.
MenuListener
The MenuListener interface provides callbacks for menu-related events.
MenuPanel
The MenuPanel class represents a panel used in the game menu.
SplashScreen
The SplashScreen class represents a panel used for displaying a splash screen with a fading animation.
Sprite
The Sprite class represents a game sprite with its position, image, hitbox, and collision logic.
TextBox
The TextBox class represents a text area for displaying text content.
Wall
The Wall class represents a wall sprite in the game.
Win
The Win class represents the panel displayed when the player wins the game.
